[['CreditRatingSearch.find_rating_standards', {'name': 'CreditRatingSearch.find_rating_standards', 'description': 'This function searches for credit rating standards based on the category.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'category', 'type': 'STRING', 'description': 'The category of credit rating standards, e.g., financial, corporate.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'standards', 'description': 'A list of up to three rating standards for the specified category.'}]}], ['CreditRatingSearch.get_rating_agencies', {'name': 'CreditRatingSearch.get_rating_agencies', 'description': 'This function retrieves a list of major credit rating agencies based on the country.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'country', 'type': 'STRING', 'description': 'The country where the rating agencies are based.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'agencies', 'description': 'A list of up to five major credit rating agencies in the specified country.'}]}], ['CreditRatingSearch.fetch_company_rating', {'name': 'CreditRatingSearch.fetch_company_rating', 'description': 'This function fetches the credit rating report for a specific company from a given rating agency.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'companyId', 'type': 'NUMBER', 'description': 'The ID of the company.'}, {'name': 'agency', 'type': 'STRING', 'description': 'The name of the rating agency.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'report', 'description': 'The credit rating report for the specified company from the given agency.'}]}], ['CreditRatingSearch.analyze_impact_on_financing', {'name': 'CreditRatingSearch.analyze_impact_on_financing', 'description': 'This function analyzes the impact of a credit rating on a company’s financing options.', 'required_parameters': [{'name': 'rating', 'type': 'STRING', 'description': 'The credit rating of the company.'}, {'name': 'industry', 'type': 'STRING', 'description': 'The industry the company operates in.'}], 'optional_parameters': [], 'return_data': [{'name': 'analysis', 'description': 'An analysis of how the credit rating affects the company’s financing options in the specified industry.'}]}]]
请生成一个解决用户问题的计划，计划应该是一个行为列表，每个行为的格式如下:

[{
    // 动作的ID
    "id": number;
    // 动作要调用的API名称
    "name": string;
    // 当前API的参数输入(JSON格式)
    "args": "str(Record<string, any>)";
}, ...
]

你可以在计划中想象参数的值，这些指令将按顺序执行。
例如，如果你想调用 `CreditRatingSearch.find_rating_standards` 并传入 `category`，你可以写下面的计划:

[{
    "id": 0,
    "name": "CreditRatingSearch.find_rating_standards",
    "args": "{'category': 'financial'}",
}, ...
]

这些参数将在执行时被替换为真实的值。请注意，参数应该是一个字符串，而不是一个字典。
请在字典的参数中使用 ''，在其他地方使用 ""，不要打印值为 None 或 null 的参数。

你应该只生成一个 JSON 格式的计划列表。列表应该是完整的计划列表，不要有 `...`。
不要生成任何解释 JSON 的文本。
